@Toc MAIN

@{B}Installation@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{B}System requirements@{UB}

The package was written on an A1230HD/68030/68882/50MHz running KS 3.0 and
Workbench 3.0.  (Yes, it is fast!  But feel free to donate any 68060
boards!!! :-))

@{B}You NEED at least Workbench 2.xx@{UB} and you need Commodore's installer.
You also, ideally, need to be able to view GuideŪ files, so use AmigaGuideŪ,
or something like that.  AmigaGuideŪ is included.

The Installer allows you to create a drawer, anywhere you like, to put
MSDOSŪ For AmigaDOSŪ into. So you COULD run it from floppy, but a hard drive
is VERY VERY strongly recommended.

The default drawer to install to will be SYSTEM, but wherever you choose
to put it, @{B}a drawer will automatically be created called MS-DOS.@{UB}

@{B}*** IMPORTANT ***   You need 400K bytes of free disk space!!!!@{UB}
                        (Now do you see why the HD is recommended!!?)

To Install the program, boot from your boot disk :-) and double click the
Install icon.  When It's all done, reboot.

This uses Commodores Installer so it should work okay.  It is rather nice
ya know...

If anyone has any big problems, please write and let me know and I'll de-bug
it and send you a fixed version!

@{B}Extras@{UB}
~~~~~~
Workbench Support (well, a little bit)

   You can start an MS-DOS DosShell, from workbench, by opening the drawer
   called MSDOS, from wherever you installed it (Try SYS:System) and double
   clicking on the nice pretty MS-DOS icon.

Wildstar (* = #?)

   To take advantage of the '*' wildstar character, you need to run
   DosWedge, included in this archive!  For more information, please
   read his docs.

   This allows you to refer to all files in DOS, as "*", rather than the
   previous "#?", which was a bit annoying.  So, whereas before you'd
   have to enter:

   Delete #?.info

   Now, you only need to enter:

   DEL *.info                                (Deletes icon files)

   So are you going to register or what!!!?
   
UNIX directory pipes (. = "" and .. = /)

   To take advantage of @{I}UNIX/MSDOS@{UI} directories such as:

    ..  <Parent directory>
    .   <Current directory>

   you will need to run @{I}DosWedge@{UI}, included in this archive!

   N.B.  You should still use AmigaDOS paths in the same way, unless you
         use Slashpatch feature as well, not recommended, because it's
         confusing!

   So whereas before you would have needed to enter, say:

   Copy from Work:#?.PIC to ""

   Now, you only need to enter:

   COPY Work:*.PIC .                (to copy all .PIC files from Work:
                                     to the current directory)

@{B}DF0:  and  DF1:  business@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
So you're sick of using DF0: and DF1: all the time, eh!!?  Well, now
you can refer to your drives as A: and B: respectively.

Yep, whereas before, you might enter:

Delete DF0:#?.info

Now, you only need enter:

DEL A:*.info                              (Deletes icon files from A:)

Just like MS-DOS :-)


@{B}CrossDOS support@{UB}
~~~~~~~~ ~~~~~~~
If you have CrossDOSŪ, you can literally read PC MS-DOS disks.  BUT!  You
won't be able to use A: and B:, because it will be configured to PC0: &
PC1:, which is a bit of a bummer.  Or is it!?  If you get your hands on
a useful utility called MultiFileSystem, you can use A: and B: with as many
disk formats as you like.  Well, almost :-)  You can find MFS on Aminet:
AmiNet/Disk/Misc/MFS...    I recommend this, too!

This would enable you to bung an MS-DOS disk into say, "Drive A" and do A: to
change the current directory to PC Drive A.

You can even do stuff like  Del *.BAT  and delete all "BAT" files!!
(If you really wanted to!).

In Fact, "MSDOSŪ For AmigaDOSŪ" Doesn't care what filesystem it operates on!
I was just pointing out that the commands work on MS-DOS disks just as well!
@EndNode

@Node MSDOS_COMMANDS
@Next MSDOS_DISTRIBUTION
@Prev MSDOS_INSTALLATION
@Toc MAIN

@{B}Commands@{UB}
~~~~~~~~

   Okay, I've installed it, I've re-booted and opened a SHELL, now what?

Well, here's a list of some AmigaDOS and their new MS-DOS equivalents:

@{U}MS-DOS@{UU}                          @{U}AmigaDOS@{UU}

A:                              Cd (DF0:)
B:                              Cd (DF1:)
Attrib <filename> <protection>  Protect <filename> <protection>
Backup <drive> <filename>       DMS Read <filename> from <drive> CMODE HEAVY2
Buffers <drive> [buffers]       AddBuffers <drive> [buffers]
Call <filename>                 Execute <filename>
Cd\                             Cd /
Cd/                             Cd /
Cd..                            Cd /
ChDir [dir]                     Cd [dir]
ChkDsk                          DiskDoctor (?)
Choice <prompt>                 Ask <prompt>
Cls                             Echo "<CTRL L>" or Amiga Z on KingCON
Country <keymapid>              Setmap <keymapid>
Date [date]                     Date [[date][time]]
DeFrag                          ReOrg *
Del <filename>                  Delete <filename> quiet
Del.                            DEL.
DelTree <dirname>               Delete <dirname> all quiet
EdLin                           MEmacs (or Ed?)
Erase                           Delete <filename> force quiet
Expand <arcname> <destination>  LHA e,x <arcname> <destination/> [patt] *
       [patt]
Exit                            EndCLI >NIL:
FC                              DIF
FDisk                           HDToolBox
FF                              Search #? #?[]#? all quiet quick file pattern
Find                            Search #? []
Format                          Format DRIVE [] NAME [] FFS INTL NOICONS...
Goto                            Skip <label> BACK
Install                         Resident
KeyBuk                          {No implemented function}
Label <device> [name]           Relabel <device> <name>
Map                             MAP
Md                              Makedir
Mem                             Avail
MKDir                           Makedir
Mode                            Prefs:Preferences
Pause                           Ask "Press [RETURN] to continue.."
PConsole                        Printmanager *
Print                           Printfiles -f
QCd                             QCD
Rd <dirname>                    Delete <dirname> quiet
Rem                             ;  (Remark!)
Ren <oldname> <newname>         Rename <oldname> <newname> quiet
Restore <filename> <drive>      DMS write <filename> TO <drive>
RmDir                           Delete
Set                             SetEnv
SetVer                          Version
Stacks                          Stack
Time [time]                     Date [[date][time]]
Ver                             Version
Vol                             Which
VSafe                           Virus_Checker n *
Win                             LoadWB >NIL:     then    EndCLI >NIL:
XCopy                           Copy CLONE NOREQ

@{U}Key@{UU}

*  =    Indicates that an extra program is required of that name for the
        instruction to work.

@{I}That's all folks!!@{UI}
@EndNode

